result.execSummary:
The defendant Christopher A Philipp was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
*Court finds defendant ineligible for the Substance Abuse Program on Count 1
**Per Court Order filed on 11/21/17 clarification:  The Court's intent and order is the 2 years condition time served be applied at the start of Count 1, Defendant is eligible to enroll in SAP/ERP on or after 8/11/18

superMiscConds.notes:
*Pay restitution joint/several with co-defendant, Jason Higgins 
Restitution on 15CF471 in the amount of $170 and on 15CF476 in the amount of $12,456.63
*25% of all moneys deposited into the defendants prison account shall be applied to the payment of fines, costs & restitution in this file.  If any fines, costs & restitution remain outstanding at the end of the confinement portion of this sentence, then the remaining balances shall be paid as a condition of extended supervision.

*Obtain and maintain full-time employment until restitution is paid in full and then maintain full-time employment or schooling or a combination of both equaling full-time.  Court will allow agent to decide if Defendant attends schooling before restitution is paid.
*Do not possess or consume alcohol or be on premises where alcohol is served/sold as its primary business except within scope of your employment.

*No contact with Jason Higgins
*No contact with Feltz Manufacturing, R&J Auto Sports, Service Transport, Inc., Town of Linwood Town Hall/Garage, Town of Carson Hall, Altenburg Dairy, Tailored Stone and Cintas or be on their property 
*Do not pawn, salvage etc. without agent's prior written approval
*Maintain absolute sobriety 
*Comply with any other assessments, treatment and programming as deemed appropriate by the agent, Compass Assessments and the DOC
*Sign release of information forms for offender's assessments, medications/pharmacies and treatment so agent can monitor compliance 
*Use one pharmacy and advise agent of this
*Consume controlled substances as prescriped by a doctor
*Pay all court ordered financial obligations in full 90 days prior to discharge, work out payment plan with agent 
*Provide DNA for testing, if not already completed
*Complete an AODA & comply with treatment recommendations.
